==History ==
The Skinner surname is likely occupational in orgin.  A skinner being one who removes the skin from animals.  The skin, fur, or meat is then  sold or kept for personal use.

Common variations on the Skinner name are Skiner, Skinners, and Skynners.

== Crest ==
The skinner family crest consists of a black shield with a gold colored [[chevron]].  Three silver [[griffin|qriffins]]' heads surround the chevorn.  Above the shield (and sometimes a helmet) is a forth griffon's head holding a red severed head in its beak.  

The Family motto commonly inscribed below the famly crest is                                  'Sanguis Et Vulnera' wish means 'Blood And Wounds'.

